  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the air fryer to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together coconut milk, fish sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, Thai red chili peppers, ginger, lime juice, coriander, and salt.",
    "Add the chicken strips to the marinade and toss to coat.",
    "Let the chicken marinate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours in the refrigerator.",
    "Remove the chicken from the marinade, letting any excess liquid drip off.",
    "Air-fry the chicken in batches until crispy and cooked through, about 12-15 minutes per batch.",
    "Meanwhile, prepare the peanut sauce by whisking together peanut butter, tahini, fish sauce, and lime juice.",
    "Serve the crispy chicken with the spiced peanut sauce and garnish with chopped coriander.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
